Privacy Policy for Tisimu

Effective date: 22 May 2026

1. Introduction
Welcome to Tisimu ("we", "our", "us"). We are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our mobile application Tisimu (the "App").

2. Information We Collect
- Account Information: When you create an account, we collect your email address and a password (securely hashed). If you sign in with Google, we receive your name and email address from Google.
- User Content: Any content you voluntarily create within the App, such as comments in communities, liturgy items, announcements, or profile information.
- Usage Data: We may collect anonymous usage data (e.g., which features you use) to improve the App. This data is not linked to your identity.

3. How We Use Your Information
- To provide and maintain the App (authentication, community features, syncing).
- To send you password reset emails or important service notifications.
- To improve the App based on usage patterns.
- To respond to your support requests.

4. Data Storage and Security
All data is stored securely using Firebase (a Google service). Firebase implements industry‑standard security measures. Your password is never stored in plain text. We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties.

5. Sharing Your Information
We do not share your personal information with any third parties except:
- When required by law.
- To protect our rights or the safety of users.
- With your explicit consent.

6. Your Rights
- You can update your profile information (display name, password) at any time.
- You can delete your account by contacting us. Deletion will remove all your personal data from our active databases.
- You can request a copy of the data we hold about you.

7. Children’s Privacy
Tisimu is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy in the App or via email.

